Le mardi 08 novembre 2005 à 11:58 -0800, Kent Beck a écrit :
&gt; Elliotte,
&gt; 
&gt; Thank you for your perspective. I understand that multiple releases would solve the problem of premature commitment to flexibility that later becomes an uncomfortable constraint. I was asking how to make multiple releases when our JAR file gets incorporated with third-party products. My first choice would be some kind of automatic update mechanism. If I understand your suggestion correctly, you are suggesting that I just don&#39;t worry about updating JUnit, as people who are interested in writing new Runners are motivated enough to go get the new release. I will give up on the update mechanism if necessary, but first I woulk like to know if anyone out there had experiences with a simple, reliable way to automatically update releases.
&gt; 
&gt; Sincerely yours,
&gt; 
&gt; Kent Beck
&gt; Three Rivers Institute
